The article discusses the 50th anniversary of the Roe v. Wade decision, which protected a woman's constitutional right to choose. It highlights that the decision was a balanced one with broad national support and had been upheld by justices appointed by both Democratic and Republican presidents. However, seven months ago, a conservative majority on the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade, putting the health and lives of women at risk. The article emphasizes that this decision opens the door for challenges to other fundamental freedoms, such as access to contraception and the right to marry. It mentions that millions of women now live in states with extreme abortion bans. The Biden administration is committed to defending reproductive rights and has issued executive orders to protect access to care, improve safety, and ensure accurate information is available. The article calls on Congress to pass legislation to codify the protections of Roe v. Wade. President Biden proclaims January 22, 2023, as the 50th Anniversary of the Roe v. Wade Decision and urges Americans to honor advocates, recognize the impact of the decision, and work towards restoring the right to choose.